  "prompt": "How many questions are asked on Quora each minute on average?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Quora has not publicly disclosed specific, up-to-date metrics detailing the exact number of questions asked on its platform each minute. However, based on available information and historical data, we can provide an estimated range.\n\n### Estimated Activity Levels\n\n- **Monthly Active Users (MAU):** Quora has reported having hundreds of millions of monthly active users. For context, as of a few years ago, Quora cited over 300 million MAUs.\n\n- **Questions Per Day:** While exact daily question volumes fluctuate, it's reasonable to estimate that Quora handles **tens of thousands to hundreds of thousands of questions each day**. This range accounts for the platform's global user base and its continuous growth.\n\n### Breaking It Down Per Minute\n\nUsing the above estimates:\n\n- **Lower Estimate:** If Quora receives **50,000 questions per day**, this translates to approximately **35 questions per minute** (50,000 \u00f7 1,440 minutes per day).\n\n- **Higher Estimate:** If the platform handles **500,000 questions per day**, that's roughly **350 questions per minute**.\n\n### Factors Influencing Question Volume\n\nSeveral factors can influence the number of questions asked on Quora each minute:\n\n1. **Time Zones:** Peak activity times align with when the most users are online globally.\n2. **Current Events:** Major news or trending topics can spur an increase in related questions.\n3. **Platform Features:** New features or prompts by Quora might encourage more user engagement.\n4. **User Growth:** Ongoing growth in Quora\u2019s user base naturally leads to more questions being posted.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nWhile it's challenging to provide an exact figure without official data from Quora, it's reasonable to surmise that the platform facilitates **dozens to hundreds of questions per minute** on average. For precise and current statistics, reaching out directly to Quora or consulting their official reports and press releases would be the best approach.",
